A hearty spoon of velvety mashed potato sits alongside pan-fried covered in a spicy
cheese coating in this recipe. Tender baby corn and a sprinkling of vibrant chives round
out an exciting and nourishing weeknight meal.

== Mashed Potato ==

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water with @salt{} for the @potatoes{3}.
Chop the potatoes into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot off the heat.
Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} or @water{}. Mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.
Cover to keep warm.

== Baby Corn ==

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @chives{5%grams} (use scissors if you prefer).

Halve the @baby corn{150%grams} lengthways.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the baby corn and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{3-4%mins}.
Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and set aside. Wipe and return the pan to
medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

== Hake ==

Once the pan is hot, add the @hake{250%grams}. Season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

Cook on one side for ~{4-5%mins}. Turn over and cook on the other side for
~{4-5%mins} more.

In the final 2 mins of cooking time, spread the @gochujang paste{1%sachet}
(use less if you don't like spice) over the fish.

Sprinkle on the @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%grams} then cover the pan
with a #lid{}. Cook for remaining time, ~{2%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish. Fish is cooked when
> opaque in the centre.

== To Serve ==

Divide the creamy mashed potato and baby corn between plates.

Serve the cheesy spiced fish alongside.

Drizzle the @honey{1%sachet} over the fish.

Finish with a sprinkling of chopped chives.